  It is accepted that two or three AT weapons should be 
assigned to destroy one target in conducting direct fire on the 
FEBA and in the immediate depth of defense in the period of fire 
preparation of the assault. 
  In launching an attack from immediate contact with the 
enemy, 
three Metis ATGM's are used for this purpose in a BTR-equipped 
MRC. In a BMP-equipped company and in a tank company 50-60 
percent of tanks and BMP's are used. The above companies can 
destroy up to 5-6 targets with their own assets. 
  A BTR-equipped MRB in the defense may use 6 Metis ATGM's, 6 
Fagot ATGM's, 1 SPG-9 and 18 RPG-7's in aligning the battle 
formation in two echelons. There is a total of 30 AT weapons 
which can be used to destroy around 30 assaulting enemy tanks. 
  Capabilities of motorized rifle and tank subunits to combat 
enemy tanks in repelling a counterattack and in the defense are 
given in Table 3. 


